Directed by: David Butler Actors: Janet Gaynor, Charles Farrell, Marjorie White Production Company: Fox Film Corporation Release Date: 18 April 1930 (Ireland) Aspect Ratio: 1.20 : 1 Molly and Bee, sweet young 'working girls,' live in a cheap room over a New York grocery store. Molly's idol, wealthy Jack Cromwell, lives in a Long Island mansion but is markedly less happy, since his fianc√©e Jane won't discourage her other admirers. Fleeing in his car, Jack ends up in an urban block party where he meets you-know-who.
